Let's now calculate the monthly rate.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Monthly rate} &=\dfrac{\text{0.059}}{\text{12}}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{0.49\%}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore the monthly rate of the contract is 0.49%.

Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity due.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV of Annuity Due} &= \dfrac{\$57,500} {\left(1+0.0049\right)}
\\[10pt]
 &= \dfrac{\$57,500} {1.0049}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$57,219.62}
\end{aligned}$$

Based on our calculation, the present value of the annuity due is $57,219.62.
